Staphylococcus aureus (SA) healthcare-associated infections (HAI) cause significant morbidity and mortality.

 SA causes 15% of all HAI and 30% of surgical site infections (SSIs).

 Each year over 40 million Americans undergo operations, 1-10% of whom will acquire SSIs.

 Such infections double the length of hospitalization and risk of dying, and increase U.

