 health care costs by $5-10 billion/year.

 We need effective interventions to prevent SSIs caused by either methicillin-susceptible (MSSA) or methicillin-resistant (MRSA) strains.

 Nasal carriers of SA (25-30% of adults) have a 2-14 times greater risk than non-carriers of acquiring an SA SSI.

 A potential prevention approach is routine pre-operative screening of patients, followed by decolonization of identified SA carriers.

